                <head>No. 178.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hitt</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Angell</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-09-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 10, 1881</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 125.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 182 of July 16 last, reporting
                    your further steps in the matter of the Danish Telegraph Company’s monopoly
                    scheme has been received.</p>
                <p>Your letter to Prince Kung and your efforts to prevent the grant of the telegraph
                    monopoly of the Chinese coast are approved. Such a monopoly would be prejudicial
                    to our interests and contrary to our idea of the true interests of China.</p>
                <p>I am, sir,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ROBERT R. HITT,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary</hi>,</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
